org.springframework.cloud.service

Class AbstractCloudServiceConnectorFactory<S>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.beans.factory.config.AbstractFactoryBean<S>
      • org.springframework.cloud.service.AbstractCloudServiceConnectorFactory<S>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - The service type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Aware, BeanClassLoaderAware, BeanFactoryAware, DisposableBean, FactoryBean<S>, InitializingBean, CloudServiceConnectorFactory<S>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CassandraClusterFactory, CloudDataSourceFactory, GenericCloudServiceConnectorFactory, MailSenderFactory, MongoDbFactoryFactory, RabbitConnectionFactoryFactory, RedisConnectionFactoryFactory

    public abstract class AbstractCloudServiceConnectorFactory<S>
extends AbstractFactoryBean<S>
implements CloudServiceConnectorFactory<S>
    Abstract base factory class.

    This factory uses the service creator provided through the constructor to create services. If the service name is provided it creates a service object based on the service bound to that name. Otherwise, it creates a singleton service and fails if it doesn't find a unique service of the expected type.

    Author:
    Ramnivas Laddad
